{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1781457176,"nonce":"mR4f7NCl5FRAXSVk/4Rmqd251rc=","title":"Projecting a **single nullable column** as part of a tuple projection decodes it as","message":"the bare type `T`, not `Option\u003cT\u003e` — so a `NULL` value fails to decode at runtime,\nand the projection type doesn't reflect the column's nullability. Selecting the\n**whole row** (`select(|(t,)| t)`) decodes nullable fields correctly as `Option\u003cT\u003e`\n(honoring `#[column(nullable)]`).\n\n\n```rust\nstruct Record\u003c'scope, C: ColumnMode = ColumnExpr\u003e {\n    #[column(primary_key)]\n    id: C::Type\u003c'scope, Uuid\u003e,\n    #[column(nullable)]\n    expires_at: C::Type\u003c'scope, SystemTime\u003e,\n}\n\n// Tuple projection of the nullable column: type comes out as SystemTime, not\n// Option\u003cSystemTime\u003e; a NULL row fails to decode.\nlet rows = conn.from::\u003cRecord\u003e()\n    .select(|(r,)| (r.id, r.expires_at))   // (Uuid, SystemTime)  \u003c- expected (Uuid, Option\u003cSystemTime\u003e)\n    .collect().await?;\n\n// Whole-row projection: r.expires_at is Option\u003cSystemTime\u003e (correct).\nlet rows = conn.from::\u003cRecord\u003e()\n    .select(|(r,)| r)\n    .collect().await?;\n```\n\n\nProjecting a nullable column expression should yield `Option\u003cT\u003e` (mirroring how the\nwhole-row decode treats `#[column(nullable)]`), or provide an explicit opt-in (e.g.\n`r.expires_at.nullable()`), so a nullable column can be read in a tuple projection\nwithout selecting the entire row.\n\n\nSelect the whole row (`select(|(t,)| t)`) and read fields by name; nullable fields\ncome back as `Option\u003cT\u003e`.\n\n\ngitana catalog: PAT `expires_at` / `last_used_at` are nullable columns whose values\nmust be read (legitimately NULL or set). Tuple projection decoded them as bare\n`SystemTime`; switching to whole-row projection everywhere was the fix. Minor /\nergonomic, not a blocker.","files":null}]}